This kinda stopped me from wanting to help you, but I am a kind person so.
Do what the other people said, I recommend using jdk 6_update 10.
Open up the compile.bat or what even it is and delete everything in it, then paste the following code:

@echo off COLOR 0f title Compiler. "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_05\bin\javac.exe" -cp . *.java pause
That’s the only thing that needs JDK is the part where you compile.

item.title: I have a big problem someone help me plzzzz
item.dc:creator: @slomifier slomifier
item.description:
@slomifier wrote:

The .bat files are in with the rest of your server files (like your client.java and characters folder). If you right click on a file with a .bat extension, you will see a “edit” option. If you click that, it will open the .bat 's coding in either notepad or wordpad. Once your there, you should see path that looks a lot like (if not) “C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_06” . I’m pretty sure that my version is really old and outdated, but your should look similar. To update it, you must change the “\jdk1.6.0_06” to “\jdk1.6.0_07”. (I’m pretty sure that’s the latest version. Wouldn’t mind if someone checked that for me)
